The paper deals with the problem of communication over a noisy channel, which is a classic topic in information theory (cs.IT). The channel is arbitrarily varying, which means that the adversary can choose the channel state, making it a topic in cryptography (cs.CR) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the capacity of the channel, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.MM) and statistical learning (cs.LG).
